#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:6
msgid ""
"By default tasks in playbooks block, meaning the connections stay open "
"until the task is done on each node.  This may not always be desirable, "
"or you may be running operations that take longer than the SSH timeout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:10
msgid ""
"To avoid blocking or timeout issues, you can use asynchronous mode to run"
" all of your tasks at once and then poll until they are done."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:12
msgid "The behaviour of asynchronous mode depends on the value of `poll`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:16
msgid "Avoid connection timeouts: poll > 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:18
msgid ""
"When ``poll`` is a positive value, the playbook will *still* block on the"
" task until it either completes, fails or times out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:20
msgid ""
"In this case, however, `async` explicitly sets the timeout you wish to "
"apply to this task rather than being limited by the connection method "
"timeout."
msgstr ""

