#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:39
msgid ""
"There is no default for the async time limit.  If you leave off the "
"'async' keyword, the task runs synchronously, which is Ansible's default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:44
msgid ""
"As of Ansible 2.3, async does not support check mode and will fail the "
"task when run in check mode. See :ref:`check_mode_dry` on how to skip a "
"task in check mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:50
msgid "Concurrent tasks: poll = 0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:52
msgid ""
"When ``poll`` is 0, Ansible will start the task and immediately move on "
"to the next one without waiting for a result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:54
msgid ""
"From the point of view of sequencing this is asynchronous programming: "
"tasks may now run concurrently."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:56
msgid "The playbook run will end without checking back on async tasks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../rst/user_guide/playbooks_async.rst:58
msgid ""
"The async tasks will run until they either complete, fail or timeout "
"according to their `async` value."
msgstr ""

